<reference id="reference_299721D69E564CB898B46045B0DE8285">
  <title>User profile fields</title>
  <shortdesc>This dialog contains account details about individual users. If
you are an administrator, you can change any user's account details.
</shortdesc>
  <refbody>
    
    
    <table id="table_22D15384ABD04899BA86EAD8972380E5"><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth="2.30*"/><colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth="3.61*"/><colspec colnum="3" colname="col3" colwidth="1.00*"/><thead><row><entry colname="col1">Field</entry><entry colname="col2">Description</entry><entry colname="col3">Required</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry colname="col1">First and last name</entry><entry colname="col2">Primary identifier for <ph id="jph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779_cf" conref="Reusable_Components/XMetaL_Reviewer.xml#ditacomponent_FFA8F9488B214B3B84175A411A134CE6/ph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779"></ph> to identify a user. Can contain spaces.</entry><entry colname="col3">Yes</entry></row><row><entry colname="col1">E-mail address
</entry><entry colname="col2">Email address used for notification for <ph id="kph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779_cf" conref="Reusable_Components/XMetaL_Reviewer.xml#ditacomponent_FFA8F9488B214B3B84175A411A134CE6/ph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779"></ph>
 tasks. </entry><entry colname="col3"></entry></row><row><entry colname="col1">Username </entry><entry colname="col2">Unique log on ID for <ph id="lph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779_cf" conref="Reusable_Components/XMetaL_Reviewer.xml#ditacomponent_FFA8F9488B214B3B84175A411A134CE6/ph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779"></ph>
 users that must have at least one upper case character. Cannot contain spaces or the following symbols: #, $, %, and *. </entry><entry colname="col3">Yes</entry></row><row><entry colname="col1">Short name</entry><entry colname="col2">Name that <ph id="zph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779_cf" conref="Reusable_Components/XMetaL_Reviewer.xml#ditacomponent_FFA8F9488B214B3B84175A411A134CE6/ph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779"></ph>
 uses to identify the owner of a comment
or revision. It is possible for more than one user to have the same
short name.
	
</entry><entry colname="col3">Yes</entry></row><row><entry colname="col1">Password</entry><entry colname="col2">Log on password that can contain  any characters except
spaces. Passwords must be between 4 and 12 characters in
length.

</entry><entry colname="col3">Yes</entry></row><row><entry colname="col1">Confirm Password</entry><entry colname="col2">Repeat password.</entry><entry colname="col3">Yes</entry></row><row><entry colname="col1">System role

</entry><entry colname="col2">Either user  or administrator. The
difference between the two types of users is that only <ph id="xph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779_cf" conref="Reusable_Components/XMetaL_Reviewer.xml#ditacomponent_FFA8F9488B214B3B84175A411A134CE6/ph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779"></ph>

administrators can add and edit any user account. Users
can only edit their own account in a limited way (i.e., they cannot
change their own System Role or Account Status). Only <ph id="cph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779_cf" conref="Reusable_Components/XMetaL_Reviewer.xml#ditacomponent_FFA8F9488B214B3B84175A411A134CE6/ph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779"></ph>
administrators can change these settings. </entry><entry colname="col3"></entry></row><row><entry colname="col1">Account status
</entry><entry colname="col2">Either 'Enabled' or 'Disabled'. A user's account must be
'Enabled' in order to log on to <ph id="vph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779_cf" conref="Reusable_Components/XMetaL_Reviewer.xml#ditacomponent_FFA8F9488B214B3B84175A411A134CE6/ph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779"></ph>
. Only <ph id="bph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779_cf" conref="Reusable_Components/XMetaL_Reviewer.xml#ditacomponent_FFA8F9488B214B3B84175A411A134CE6/ph_BC5271148E66415AAFD5F21793E18779"></ph>

administrators can change this setting. An administrator
cannot disable his or her own account.
</entry><entry colname="col3"></entry></row><row><entry colname="col1">Comment Text Box

</entry><entry colname="col2">Text box for adding comments. Administrators can add
comments to this box at any time. Users can add text only
to their own account's comment box; they can read comments from all
accounts. 
</entry><entry colname="col3"></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table>

  </refbody>
